    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1901-09-25T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1901-09-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="331"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d331">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hill</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Takahira</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1901-09-25">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 25, 1901</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The pressure of public business attendant upon
                    the death of President McKinley has delayed until now an acknowledgment of the
                    telegram from the Japanese minister for foreign affairs (copy of which was left
                    by you at the Department), conveying an expression of His Imperial Majesty’s
                    sympathy in view of that sad event.</p>
                <p>I shall be obliged if you will assure his excellency, in the name of the
                    Government and people of the United States, as well as in the name of the family
                    of the late President, that this message of sympathy on the part of His Majesty
                    was received with sincere and grateful appreciation.</p>
                <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">David J. Hill</hi>,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
